    {
      "scene_id": "scene_003",
      "timing": {
        "start_time": 116.8,
        "end_time": 205.6,
        "duration": 88.8
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "INT. ARTIFACT CHAMBER - LATER\n\n[Approx. Timestamp: 00:07:00]\nA vast room with a glowing crystalline ARTIFACT at the center, pulsing blue energy. Consoles spark. The team enters cautiously.\n\nKAI\n(awestruck, approaching)\nBeautiful. It's a nexus point\u2014connecting infinite timelines.\n\nHe touches a console. The artifact HUMS louder. Holographic displays activate, showing fractured images: alternate teams succeeding, failing, dying.\n\nLENA\n(hacking in)\nLogs confirm: Crew activated it, then... merged with echoes. Became something else.\n\nMARCUS\nMerged? Like, body horror?\n\nELARA\nKai, don't touch it yet. We extract data first.\n\nKAI\n(ignoring, scanning)\nToo late. Look\u2014these readings... we could control it. Jump timelines. Fix mistakes.\n\nELARA\nThat's not our mission. Corporate wants the artifact contained, not played with.\n\nKAI\nCorporate? They're idiots. Imagine: A world without the war. Or one where my family didn't die in the colony collapse.\n\nLENA\n(sympathetic)\nKai... that's heavy. But messing with timelines? Butterfly effect city.\n\nMARCUS\nYeah, like, what if we erase ourselves?\n\nThe artifact pulses brighter. More echoes appear\u2014translucent versions of the team, arguing in parallel.\n\nECHO-ELARA (faint, overlapping)\n...don't touch it...\n\nECHO-KAI\n...we must...\n\nA surge\u2014 the room shakes. Marcus trips, his hand brushes the artifact.\n\nMARCUS\nOops\u2014\n\nReality GLITCHES. The team freezes, then duplicates briefly.\n\nELARA\nMarcus! What did you do?\n\nMARCUS\nNothing! It just... pulled me.\n\nKAI\n(excited)\nIt's responding. We're linked now.\n\nCUT TO:\n",
