        "start_time": 207.6,
        "end_time": 298.4,
        "duration": 90.8
      },
      "content": {
        "text": "INT. ARTIFACT CHAMBER - ESCALATING CHAOS\n\n[Approx. Timestamp: 00:12:00]\nThe glitches worsen. Echoes solidify, interacting.\n\nECHO-LENA (to real Lena)\nIn my timeline, you invented this. But it consumed you.\n\nLENA\n(stunned)\nMe? No way. I fix things, not break universes.\n\nKAI\n(to Elara)\nCaptain, think bigger. We could merge timelines\u2014create a perfect one.\n\nELARA\nNo. That's playing god. Lena, shut it down.\n\nLENA\n(working frantically)\nTrying! But it's rewriting code on its own. AI-level intelligence?\n\nMARCUS\nGuys, look\u2014more echoes. And they're... us, but wrong.\n\nEchoes multiply: One team fights aliens (wait, aliens?), another dances absurdly, a third melts into goo.\n\nECHO-MARCUS (melting one)\nHelp... it's infinite...\n\nThe real team backs away.\n\nELARA\nThis is spiraling. Evac protocol\u2014back to the shuttle!\n\nKAI\n(rebellious)\nWait! I can control it. Just one command...\n\nHe inputs something. The artifact ROARS. A portal opens\u2014swirling void.\n\nFrom it, bizarre entities emerge: Tentacled shadows, clockwork beings, cartoonish figures.\n\nLENA\nWhat the\u2014? That's not sci-fi; that's nightmare fuel!\n\nMARCUS\n(panicking)\nAliens? Robots? Why is there a dancing pineapple echo?!\n\nELARA\nKai, you idiot! You've cracked the multiverse!\n\nKAI\n(realizing horror)\nI... thought I could select timelines. But it's all of them. Every possibility.\n\nThe room fills with chaos: Echoes clash\u2014laser fights, philosophical debates, slapstick comedy.\n\nECHO-ELARA (to real Elara)\nIn my world, you're a pirate queen. Arrr!\n\nReal Elara shoots a confused look.\n\nCUT TO:\n",
